---
description: Enforce mobile-first responsive design in all frontend components
globs: frontend/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

# Responsive Design — Mobile First

Every layout must work on a 320px-wide screen before adding breakpoints for larger sizes.

## Grids

Start at one column and scale up:

```tsx
// BAD -- forces 3 columns on all screen sizes
<div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4">

// GOOD
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
```

## Page Headers (title + actions)

Stack vertically on mobile, row on larger screens:

```tsx
// BAD -- overflows on mobile
<div className="flex items-center justify-between">

// GOOD
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
```

## Button Groups / Action Bars

Always allow wrapping:

```tsx
// BAD -- buttons overflow off screen
<div className="flex items-center gap-2">

// GOOD
<div className="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
```

## Flex Rows with Mixed Content

Side-by-side content (e.g., avatar + form) should stack on mobile:

```tsx
// BAD
<div className="flex gap-6">

// GOOD
<div className="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6">
```

## When this rule does NOT apply

- Modals and dialogs that already use a fixed `max-w-*` container
- Components that are only rendered inside a constrained parent (e.g., sidebar panels with a known width)

## General Rules

- Never use bare `grid-cols-N` (N >= 2) without a responsive base of `grid-cols-1`.
- Never use `flex justify-between` on a page header without `flex-col sm:flex-row`.
- Use `min-w-0` on flex children that contain text to allow truncation instead of overflow.
- Avoid fixed pixel widths (`w-[400px]`) on containers with dynamic content — use `max-w-*` or percentages.
